    public interface CLImmutable
extends Immutable
    An interface for immutable classes. All public fields must be final. Private and protected fields need not be final, but should not have public setter methods. Lazy evaluation of these non-public fields is allowed, but their getters should behave as if the fields were final, always returning the same result. Constructors must return a fully initialized object.
    Author:
    taraathan
